(72, 1, '2014-11-13 09:13:48', '2014-11-13 09:13:48', '<div id="slide_04">\r\n\r\n\r\n<a class="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hviMEPu7DqY"><img src="https://www.cjaviationsafety.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/slide8.png" alt="video-icon" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-262" /></a>\r\n<iframe id="player" type="text/html" width="640" height="390"  src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/hviMEPu7DqY?enablejsapi=1&controls=0&showinfo=0"   frameborder="0"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a class="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hviMEPu7DqY&controls=0" style="color:#000000; font-size:20px; text-decoration:underline;">WATCH VIDEO</a>\r\nHUMAN FACTORS\r\nCONTINUATION\r\nTRAINING\r\n</div>', 'Slide 04 - HUMAN FACTORS â CONTINUATION TRAINING', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'slide-04-human-factors-continuation-training', '', '', '2015-03-25 09:33:16', '2015-03-25 09:33:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aviation-safety/?post_type=aviation-questions&#038;p=72', 3, 'aviation-questions', '', 0),
(73, 1, '2014-11-13 09:14:51', '2014-11-13 09:14:51', '[rev_slider slide5]	\r\n<!--\r\n<ul class="big_ul">\r\n<li>The purpose of Human Factors Continuation Training is primarily to ensure that staff remain current in terms of Human Factors and also to collect feedback on Human Factors issues. \r\n<p class="bold_red_italic">Ref:- Maintenance and Continuing Airworthiness Mandates (M&CA)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[delay_show]\r\n<ul class="big_ul">\r\n<li>\r\nContinuation Training should not take the form of repetition of syllabus items just for the sake of it - the opportunity should be used to address real, topical issues which are of concern. Whilst there are still Human Factors problems to be resolved and maintenance errors occurring, continuation training is key to maintaining staff buy-in year on year. \r\n<p class="bold_red_italic">Ref:- CAP 716 (Civil Aviation Publications)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[delay_show]\r\n<ul class="big_ul">\r\n<li>\r\nReference to the above are also outlined in the Military Aviation Authority (MAA)\r\n<p class="bold_red_italic">Ref:- RA4807(4)  and RA1440 (2).  (Regulatory Articles)  </p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n-->', 'Slide 05 - HUMAN FACTORS CONTINUATION TRAINING', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'slide-05-human-factors-continuation-training', '', '', '2015-03-09 15:20:16', '2015-03-09 15:20:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aviation-safety/?post_type=aviation-questions&#038;p=73', 4, 'aviation-questions', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2014-11-13 09:15:23', '2014-11-13 09:15:23', '[row class="slide_06"]\r\n[column_3]\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-155 alignright" src="http://localhost/aviation-safety/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/slide_06.png" alt="slide_06" width="186" height="358" />\r\n[/column_3]\r\n[column_9 class="big_centered_p"]\r\n\r\nM&amp;CA\r\n\r\n(MAINTANANCE &amp; CONTINUING AIRWORTHINESS)\r\n\r\nPOLICY AND MANDATE REQUIREMENTS\r\n[/column_9]\r\n[/row]', 'Slide 06 - M&CA', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'slide-06-mca', '', '', '2014-11-14 07:38:41', '2014-11-14 07:38:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aviation-safety/?post_type=aviation-questions&#038;p=74', 5, 'aviation-questions', '', 0),
