(84, 1, '2014-11-13 09:20:20', '2014-11-13 09:20:20', '<img src="http://localhost/aviation-safety/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/slide_16.png" alt="slide_16" width="2000" height="1195" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-174" />', 'Slide 16 - THE CONCEPT OF HUMAN FACTORS', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'slide-16-the-concept-of-human-factors', '', '', '2014-11-14 08:08:59', '2014-11-14 08:08:59', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aviation-safety/?post_type=aviation-questions&#038;p=84', 15, 'aviation-questions', '', 0),
(85, 1, '2014-11-13 09:20:36', '2014-11-13 09:20:36', '<ul class="big_ul">\r\n<li>An effective âJust Cultureâ will create a working environment where individuals are encouraged to contribute pro-actively to providing essential safety related information and where they are commended for owning up to mistakes in their honest endeavour to do their best. </li>\r\n<li>It should promote a sense that they will be treated fairly and with complete integrity while the organisation investigates why mistakes have been made in a way to prevent it happening again. </li>\r\n<li>A âJust Cultureâ, open an honest reporting, and management of information to support decision-making are essential foundations of effective error management.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Slide 17 - JUST CULTURE', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'slide-17-just-culture', '', '', '2014-11-14 08:10:08', '2014-11-14 08:10:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aviation-safety/?post_type=aviation-questions&#038;p=85', 16, 'aviation-questions', '', 0),
